I thought the point in the sweep method was to show it&#39;s not 
complicated, and no exotic technoglogy required!

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot; RetroCom&quot; &lt;vfp19968@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Frank, I&#39;m not misleading anyone, the optical microphone using a 
flame in and of itself works very well in the capture of Spirit 
voices. I don&#39;t know exactly why, after almost two years I am still 
studying it although I can speculate it could because there is a lot 
going on during it&#39;s use. Change of state from liquid to vapor to 
heat and light, IR radiation, thermal noise and some processes I am 
missing or unaware of. The radio sweep is used as a source of sound 
samples, the microphone also works well using music or plain speech. 
The limited high frequency response also seems to act as a built-in 
bandpass filter. I&#39;m not using anything complicated or out of the 
reach of a Wal-Mart or K-Mart shopper. I&#39;m using an off the shelf 
oil lamp with a 3/4 inch wide flat wick, a phototransistor from 
Radio Shack and an FM radio.  There is more to the flame microphone 
then modulated light, I can modulate the DC feeding a flashlight or 
and LED and not get the same results. Here is an exchange using the 
optical microphone and FM radio sweep, my voice is reduced by 10db.
&gt; Dave: (NOT EVP) &#39;How many of you are are testing today?&#39;
&gt; 
&gt; Response : &quot;Fourty Seven&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; Dave: &#39;Please state your name, thank you&#39;
&gt; 
&gt; Response : &quot;Ingrid&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Maybe it&#39;s dumb question, but..................
&gt; 
&gt;  If the flame is being &quot;modulated&quot; by air movements caused by 
&gt; atmosphereic sound pressure waves, so the flame varies at an audio 
&gt; rate, then those flame variations are picked up via the photo 
&gt; transistor and converted to electrical signals...what&#39;s the 
difference 
&gt; between the optical mic, and an accoustic mic? And why would one 
want 
&gt; to introduce yet another seemingly exotic piece of hardware?
&gt; 
&gt;  I know it&#39;s interesting, but it really has nothing to do with how 
to 
&gt; get ghost voices, and maybe misleading to some that are searching 
for 
&gt; that magic technology. 
&gt; 
&gt;  
&gt;    Frank
&gt;
